    <title>A Lower Bound For Depths of Powers of Edge Ideals</title>
    <summary>  Let $G$ be a graph and let $I$ be the edge ideal of $G$. Our main results in
this article provide lower bounds for the depth of the first three powers of
$I$ in terms of the diameter of $G$. More precisely, we show that ${\rm{depth}}
\ R/I^t \geq \lceil{\frac{d-4t+5}{3}} \rceil +p-1$, where $d$ is the diameter
of $G$, $p$ is the number of connected components of $G$ and $1 \leq t \leq 3$.
As an application of our result we obtain the corresponding lower bounds for
the Stanley depth of the first three powers of $I$.
</summary>
